                        BURNING DVDS
DVD x Copy from 321 Studios is a $99.99 program that uses
Windows XP or 2000 computer to make a copy of movies or
other DVDs, BusinessWeek reports.  There is a 
long-recognized "fair use" right under copyright law for
individuals to copy material for their personal use, but
the movie industry thinks the program violates the Digital
Millennium Copyright Act of 1998.  The Chesterfield, 
Mo.-based company, disagrees. A message stating the disk
is a copy made for personal use only, is the first thing
a viewer sees and if a viewer tries to make a copy of a 
copy, it will fail.  The duplicate also contains a hidden
digital "watermark" that can trace any disk back to the 
specific copy of DVD x Copy used to create it.  

                   
